<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,481,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,324,578,602]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
The determination label (
<figureCitation box="[643,729,578,602]" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="4.[192,288,1647,1669]" captionTargetBox="[221,1410,192,1631]" captionTargetId="figure-95@4.[221,1410,192,1631]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 1–6. Six species of Onciderini. Fig. 1. Cacostola variegata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 2. Charoides antennata antennata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 3. Cylicasta nysa Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 4. Hesycha crucifera Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 5. Hesychotypa archippa Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels). Fig. 6. Hesychotypa subfasciata Dillon and Dillon (a, dorsal habitus; b, labels)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5168903" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5168903/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
) indicates that L. S. Dillon and E. S. Dillon identified this specimen as “ 
<taxonomicName box="[359,608,610,634]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hesycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paupercula">
<emphasis box="[359,608,610,634]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Hesycha paupercula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.” Later, in their description of 
<taxonomicName box="[991,1211,610,634]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hesycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crucifera">
<emphasis box="[991,1211,610,634]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Hesycha crucifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the same authors (
<bibRefCitation author="Dillon, L. S. &amp; E. S. Dillon" box="[200,483,641,666]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" pagination="59 - 79" refId="ref3277" refString="Dillon, L. S., and E. S. Dillon. 1952. The tribe Onciderini. Supplementary notes. Annals of the Entomological Society of America 45: 59 - 79." type="journal article" year="1952">Dillon and Dillon 1952</bibRefCitation>
) stated “an examination of a specimen compared to the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hesycha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paupercula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Hesycha paupercula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that the species described in the above citation was not actually that form but a new species, which is herewith named. 
<typeStatus box="[619,734,706,730]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Holotype</typeStatus>
: Male, Nova Friburgo, R.J., 
<collectingCountry box="[1080,1158,706,730]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Brazil</collectingCountry>
; M.C.Z.”
</paragraph>
